# @dukkani/ui Package

## Purpose

The `ui` package contains shared UI components built with shadcn/ui and Radix UI. It provides a consistent design system across all applications.

## Structure

```
packages/ui/src/
├── components/        # UI components
│   └── {component}.tsx
├── hooks/             # Component hooks
│   └── use-{hook}.ts
├── lib/               # Utilities
│   └── utils.ts       # cn() utility
└── styles/            # Global styles
    └── globals.css
```

## Components

### Location
`packages/ui/src/components/`

### File Naming
`{component}.tsx` (kebab-case)

### Pattern

Components follow shadcn/ui patterns with Radix UI primitives and Tailwind CSS styling.

```typescript
import { Slot } from "@radix-ui/react-slot";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "../lib/utils";

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground",
        outline: "border bg-background",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-9 px-4",
        sm: "h-8 px-3",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  },
);

function Button({
  className,
  variant,
  size,
  asChild = false,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"button"> &
  VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> & {
    asChild?: boolean;
  }) {
  const Comp = asChild ? Slot : "button";

  return (
    <Comp
      className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}

export { Button, buttonVariants };
```

### Component Naming

- File: `{component}.tsx` (kebab-case)
- Export: `PascalCase` component name
- Variants: Export variant function if using CVA

### Best Practices

- Use `cn()` utility for className merging
- Use CVA (class-variance-authority) for variant-based styling
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessibility
- Export both component and variants when using CVA
- Use `asChild` prop pattern for composition
- Support all standard HTML attributes via `...props`

## Utilities

### Location
`packages/ui/src/lib/utils.ts`

### Pattern

The `cn()` utility combines classnames using `clsx` and `tailwind-merge`.

```typescript
import { clsx } from "clsx";
import { twMerge } from "tailwind-merge";

export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
}
```

### Usage

```typescript
import { cn } from "@dukkani/ui/lib/utils";

<div className={cn("base-classes", condition && "conditional-classes")} />
```

